At 12:40 PM 6/29/2004 +0100, you wrote:
>Hi all,
>
>Does anybody know if it's possible to use the 'atoizilliontext' expression
>to provide corrective feedback for experiments involving typed responses?
>Otherwise, is there an alternative way to provide such feedback?

   Yes, you'll have to design your own feedback routine as outlined in the 
branching documentation.  You'll want to load a counter using 
atoizilliontext and use the keyword that appends a counters value to a 
frame's display <AppendCounter> or some such thing.

